description:
The internet was once a vast digital frontier of endless human created content. The World Wide Web connected us, until corporations decided their profit margins mattered more than Tim Berners-Lee's vision of an open web. Now we're trapped on the same few websites, force fed algorithmic content and AI generated slop. Anonymous users predicted this years ago with what they called Dead Internet Theory. From bot armies manipulating conversations to AI generated content flooding every platform, the internet we once knew is disappearing.

#DeadInternetTheory

Chapters:
00:00 Intro
01:00 Dead Internet Theory
02:01 More Bots on the Internet than Humans
02:43 YouTube Bots
03:04 Bot Networks
03:40 TikTok Bots
04:07 Reddit Bots
05:21 X Bots
05:56 Meta AI Companion Bots
07:25 Facebook’s Farmville and Algorithms
08:46 Platforms as Walled Gardens
09:58 AI Slop is Taking Over
10:40 YouTube AI Generated Content
11:09 TikTok AI Generated Content
11:30 LinkedIn AI Generated Content
11:41 AI Generated Vogue Models
11:52 Dating Apps Using AI
12:45 Academia and AI
12:56 TikTok Bots Stealing YouTube Content
13:15 The Decline of Google Search
13:35 Google’s AI Overview
15:24 People Using ChatGPT As A Search Engine
15:58 Why Corporations Want A Dead Internet
17:54 What Happens When the Internet Dies?

comments.text:
Hi! Making this video made me sad. The internet used to be a glorious place filled with hidden gems. Corporate greed has destroyed what the internet was meant to be, but it's important to discuss what's happening because it affects every one of us. 

Some of you have been suggesting content ideas and giving video style/edit feedback. I really appreciate both of these. I always try to incorporate feedback and it's really cool to see that so many of you are interested in the same topics as I am. 

Also, an interesting thing happens when you record hours of yourself talking to a camera, you discover weird quirks about yourself. I've come to realize one of mine is that whenever I say years ranging from 2001-2019, I put an "and" in between. For example, in the video I say "two thousand and nine" in a previous video I said "two thousand and twelve." I didn't know I did this until I started making YouTube videos so I guess that's a fun fact about me…😅

Thanks for watching, liking, and commenting - it helps me direct where to steer the content and also how to edit the videos. 😃

I chose not to monetize.  But here I am elevating this channel well beyond all the others I dinna post on today.

One loss which makes me sad:  My family name is pretty rare.  At the start of the internet getting popular, I would get emails from random people from places around the world who had my last name.  "Hey, is it possible we're related?".  And yes, it always turned out they could trace their ancestry back to the same city in Germany that my family came from.  I actually kept in touch with a few of these far-flung relatives.

(2) if I get any email even close to that now, it's someone spamming me or phishing for profit.

comments.text:
@benbraceletspurple9108  My Daemon Ra noted it...

"⚙ Walled Garden (Proper Definition)
In tech and telecom, a walled garden refers to:

A closed platform or ecosystem where the provider controls access, functionality, and content.

This is not about AI or bots themselves — it’s about limiting what users can access within a platform.

🔒 Real-world examples:
Apple’s App Store: tightly controlled, only Apple-approved apps

Facebook: user content is accessible within the network but not freely shareable outside

Amazon Kindle: books and media locked into their own DRM ecosystem

AOL (classic): early “starter internet” where everything was trapped inside their browser/interface

So when someone misuses “walled garden” to describe bots taking over the open internet — it’s technically off-base. Bots running loose outside platforms? That’s more like digital entropy, wildfire automation, or unfenced computation — the opposite of a walled garden.

🧠 TL;DR
Walled Garden = controlled access.
Bot Flood = uncontrolled saturation.

Totally different beasts."
